  "texts": [
    "Formally,O 𝑛 = 𝑇𝑙 (𝑠 𝑛),(9)where O 𝑛 denotes the tool output in text format.",
    "Notably, the methodology described here can be adapted and applied to various other tools.• Action generation.",
    "We leverage both the guidance from the Planner module, micro-level knowledge obtained from the memory and tool to prompt the LLM of the Actor module to generate an action.",
    "For the input (H1•••𝑛-1, 𝑠 𝑛, 𝑡 𝑛) with 𝑡 𝑛 representing the thought, once we obtain the corresponding retrieval results Ψ 𝑛 𝐴 and tool analysis result 𝑂 𝑛, we can sample an action 𝑎 ′ 𝑛 from the LLM policy as follows:𝑎 ′ 𝑛 ∼ LLM(P 𝐴, Ψ 𝑛 M 𝐴, O 𝑛, H 1•••𝑛-1, 𝑠 𝑛, 𝑡 𝑛),(10)where P 𝐴 represents the task instruction for the Actor.",
    "Note that the temperature coefficient of the LLM should be set to a non-zero value, ensuring the generation of non-deterministic results.Item grounding."
